# Project Structure & Naming

## Directory Layout

```
src/
├── app/           # Next.js App Router pages/layouts ONLY
├── pages/api/     # ALL API routes (Pages Router)
├── components/    # Shared React components
├── context/       # React contexts (globalContext, optimizedContext)
├── hooks/         # Custom hooks (useDashboard, useIsMobile, useTile, etc.)
├── models/        # Mongoose models (Dashboard, Tile, Pod, User, Template)
├── utils/         # Pure helpers (safeLocalStorage, imageOptimization, etc.)
├── lib/           # Server utilities (db connection via utils.js)
├── constants/     # Shared constants
├── styles/        # Global styles
└── assets/        # Static assets
```

## Naming Conventions

| Type        | Convention | Example |
|-------------|------------|---------|
| Components  | PascalCase | `GridTiles.js`, `SideDrawer.js` |
| Hooks       | camelCase + `use` prefix | `useDashboard.js`, `useIsMobile.js` |
| API routes  | camelCase or `[param].js` | `addDashboard.js`, `[id].js` |
| Models      | PascalCase | `dashboard.js` (exports `Dashboard`) |
| Utils       | camelCase  | `safeLocalStorage.js`, `imageUpload.js` |
| Contexts    | camelCase  | `appContext.js`, `globalContext.js` |

## Component Patterns

- Use `dynamic()` with `ssr: false` for heavy client components (GridTiles, MobileGridTiles, TipTap editor)
- All page components in `src/app/` must be Client Components (`'use client'`) if they use hooks, state, or browser APIs
- API utility components (LazyModal, LazyTipTapEditor) use dynamic imports for code splitting
